{"type":"text","timestamp":1773445461553,"sessionID":"ses_316701812ffeYe5yCqGzB5GjN6","part":{"id":"prt_ce9959ba9001KQ1AbNbyn6QZpC","sessionID":"ses_316701812ffeYe5yCqGzB5GjN6","messageID":"msg_ce995909100169TnZWnU95kMfJ","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the `tdd-red-green-coercion` feature for the wombo-combo AI agent orchestration system. The feature enforces test-driven development (TDD) in the agent workflow by: (1) writing failing tests first (red phase), (2) verifying tests fail, (3) implementing code to make tests pass (green phase), (4) verifying tests pass, (5) optionally refactoring. The verification pipeline should flag commits without corresponding test changes, and build verification should run tests and check that new tests exist for new functionality.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- **Branch:** `feature/tdd-red-green-coercion`, base: `main`\n- Must detect test files and verify they exist for new source files\n- Must run tests as part of build verification\n- Must enforce red-green cycle in agent prompts and verification\n- Must NOT block features explicitly marked as non-testable (config, docs)\n- Do NOT make TDD mandatory for trivial changes (config files, documentation)\n- Use conventional commits with scope `tdd-red-green-coercion`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify at the end\n- Use `portless run` when starting servers\n- Runtime: Bun, TypeScript strict mode, ESM only\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **The core TDD implementation already exists** in the codebase. All the source modules were already written:\n   - `src/config.ts` — `TddConfig` type with `enabled`, `testCommand`, `strictTdd`, `testTimeout` fields, defaults included\n   - `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — Full TDD verification pipeline orchestrating test runner + test detection\n   - `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — Git diff parsing, test file matching, exclusion logic (barrels, types-only, .d.ts), coverage reporting\n   - `src/lib/test-runner.ts` — Command execution, output parsing (bun/jest formats), error extraction\n   - `src/lib/verifier.ts` — Full verification pipeline integrating build + browser + TDD (`runFullVerification`)\n   - `src/lib/prompt.ts` — TDD red-green-refactor instructions injected when `tdd.enabled` is true\n   - `src/commands/verify.ts` — CLI flags `--skip-tests`, `--strict-tdd` wired\n   - `src/commands/launch.ts` — `handleBuildVerification` reports TDD results\n   - `src/index.ts` — CLI arg parsing for `--skip-tests`, `--strict-tdd`\n\n2. **What was missing:** Unit tests for the TDD-specific modules (test-detection, test-runner, tdd-verifier, prompt TDD injection)\n\n3. **Pre-existing test failures:** 12 tests in `tests/worktree.test.ts` and `tests/worktree-filtering.test.ts` fail due to a worktree path scheme change (pre-existing, not caused by this work)\n\n4. **Pre-existing LSP errors:** `tests/config.test.ts` has errors about `worktreePrefix` property not existing on the git config type (pre-existing)\n\n5. **`isTypesOnlyFile` heuristic:** Enum body lines (e.g., `Red,`) don't match the property regex, so enums are NOT treated as types-only. `declare module` with `export function` inside is also rejected. Tests were adjusted accordingly.\n\n6. **`extractTestErrorSummary` off-by-one:** The function combines stdout + \"\\n\" + stderr, adding an extra line, so \"last 30 lines\" from 50 lines of stdout starts at line 22, not 21.\n\n7. **`Feature` type is aliased as `Task`** (`export type Feature = Task` in `src/lib/tasks.ts`). The `TaskStatus` type must be used for the `status` field — `\"ready\"` is not a valid `TaskStatus`.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. ✅ **tests/test-detection.test.ts** — 59 tests covering `isTestFile`, `isBarrelFile`, `isTypesOnlyFile`, `isExcludedFile`, `filterSourceFiles`, `findTestFiles`, `detectTests`, `DEFAULT_TEST_DETECTION_CONFIG` (committed: `1582dc3`)\n2. ✅ **tests/test-runner.test.ts** — 30 tests covering `parseTestCounts` (bun/jest/unparseable formats), `extractTestErrorSummary`, `runTests` integration tests (committed: `1e0373a`)\n3. ✅ **tests/tdd-verifier.test.ts** — 25 tests covering `runTddVerification` (skip behaviors, test execution, detection, strict mode), `extractTddErrorSummary`, `renderTddVerificationReport` (committed: `3b76cdb`)\n\n### In Progress:\n4. 🔧 **tests/prompt-tdd.test.ts** — Written but has a **TypeScript error**: `Type '\"ready\"' is not assignable to type 'TaskStatus'`. Need to check valid `TaskStatus` values and fix the `makeFeature()` helper. File is saved but NOT committed.\n\n### Remaining:\n5. ⬜ Fix the TSError in `tests/prompt-tdd.test.ts`, run it, and commit\n6. ⬜ Run full test suite (`bun test`) to verify all new tests pass alongside existing ones\n7. ⬜ Run `bun run build` to verify build passes\n8. ⬜ Final commit if needed\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Source files (already existed, read for understanding):\n- `src/config.ts` — WomboConfig, TddConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n- `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — TDD verification pipeline (runTddVerification, reports)\n- `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — Git diff parsing, test file matching, exclusion logic\n- `src/lib/test-runner.ts` — Test command execution, output parsing\n- `src/lib/verifier.ts` — Full verification pipeline (build + browser + TDD)\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Agent prompt generation with TDD injection\n- `src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task/Feature types (Feature = Task alias, line 119; TaskStatus type)\n- `src/commands/verify.ts` — Verify command with --skip-tests, --strict-tdd\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — handleBuildVerification with TDD reporting (line 305+)\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point with TDD arg parsing\n\n### Test files (created in this session):\n- `tests/test-detection.test.ts` — ✅ 59 tests, committed\n- `tests/test-runner.test.ts` — ✅ 30 tests, committed\n- `tests/tdd-verifier.test.ts` — ✅ 25 tests, committed\n- `tests/prompt-tdd.test.ts` — 🔧 Written, has TSError on line 29 (`\"ready\"` not valid TaskStatus), needs fix\n\n### Existing test files (for reference/context):\n- `tests/config.test.ts` — Has pre-existing LSP errors about `worktreePrefix`\n- `tests/` — 10 pre-existing test files\n\n### Config files:\n- `package.json` — scripts: `build`, `test`, `typecheck`\n- `AGENTS.md` — Development conventions\n- `tsconfig.json`","time":{"start":1773445461551,"end":1773445461551}}}
