{"type":"text","timestamp":1773445842463,"sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","part":{"id":"prt_ce99bdc39002g8D4ordgqSiH08","sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","messageID":"msg_ce99bd1db001o2LKnyTv4Eddmv","type":"text","text":"Let me analyze the existing code more deeply to understand what gaps exist. The task says to enforce TDD red-green development cycle. Let me look at what's already there vs what needs to be added/enhanced:\n\n**What exists:**\n1. `config.ts` - `TddConfig` with `enabled`, `testCommand`, `strictTdd`, `testTimeout` ✓\n2. `test-detection.ts` - Detects test files for source files, git diff analysis ✓\n3. `test-runner.ts` - Runs test command, parses output ✓\n4. `tdd-verifier.ts` - Combines test-runner + test-detection results ✓\n5. `verifier.ts` - Full verification pipeline with TDD step ✓\n6. `prompt.ts` - TDD instructions in agent prompts ✓\n7. `verify.ts` command - CLI flags for `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` ✓\n\n**Gaps I identify:**\n1. No tests for any of the TDD modules (test-detection, test-runner, tdd-verifier)\n2. No test for the TDD prompt generation\n3. Non-testable file exclusion could be enhanced (docs, config files specifically)\n4. The red-green cycle verification could be stronger in prompts\n5. The test-detection doesn't explicitly exclude `.md`, `.json`, `.yml` config files (it does filter by `src/` dir, but the constraint says \"explicitly marked as non-testable (config, docs)\")\n\nLet me start by writing the tests (TDD approach - following the project's own philosophy).","time":{"start":1773445842462,"end":1773445842462}}}
