{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773446100958,"sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","part":{"id":"prt_ce99ff7dd001M3c6lbUX0Xrjfa","sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","messageID":"msg_ce99fed15001J3u9HrOFsiqhaC","type":"step-start","snapshot":"0c3d6dad328cbdb2d09f952ba3818e54b20c1ada"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773446136659,"sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","part":{"id":"prt_ce99ff7de001a2tgAV3ImKzk95","sessionID":"ses_316650d1dffespdzjLs3PfWdD3","messageID":"msg_ce99fed15001J3u9HrOFsiqhaC","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement TDD red-green coercion for the wombo-combo AI agent orchestration system. The feature enforces test-driven development in the agent workflow: agents must write failing tests first (red), verify they fail, implement code to pass (green), verify they pass, then optionally refactor. The verification pipeline should flag commits without corresponding test changes, run tests as part of build verification, and not block non-testable changes (config, docs).\n\n## Instructions\n\n- **Branch:** `feature/tdd-red-green-coercion` (already checked out)\n- **Build command:** `bun run build` — must pass before task is complete\n- **Test command:** `bun test`\n- Use conventional commits with scope `tdd-red-green-coercion`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory\n- Do NOT make TDD mandatory for trivial changes (config files, documentation)\n- Must detect test files and verify they exist for new source files\n- Must run tests as part of build verification\n- Must enforce red-green cycle in agent prompts and verification\n- Use `portless run` when starting servers\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The codebase already has substantial TDD infrastructure:\n  - `src/config.ts` — `TddConfig` with `enabled`, `testCommand`, `strictTdd`, `testTimeout` fields\n  - `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — Detects test files for source files via git diff, checks for barrel/types-only/d.ts exclusions\n  - `src/lib/test-runner.ts` — Runs test commands, parses Bun/Jest output formats\n  - `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — Combines test-runner + test-detection into structured results\n  - `src/lib/verifier.ts` — Full verification pipeline (build + browser + TDD)\n  - `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Already has TDD red-green-refactor instructions injected when `tdd.enabled` is true\n  - `src/commands/verify.ts` — CLI with `--skip-tests` and `--strict-tdd` flags\n- The `isTypesOnlyFile` heuristic doesn't handle enum member bodies (bare values like `Red,` don't match the property regex), so enum files are NOT considered types-only\n- Pre-existing test failures exist in `tests/arg-parsing.test.ts` (default command changed to \"tui\"), `tests/config.test.ts` (references `worktreePrefix` which doesn't exist in type), and `tests/features.test.ts` (completion===0 guard removed) — these are NOT related to this task\n- Build passes cleanly: `bun build src/index.ts --outdir dist --target node`\n- The `git` config type doesn't have `worktreePrefix` — some existing tests reference it incorrectly (pre-existing issue)\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. **Analyzed the full codebase** — read all key files (config, test-detection, test-runner, tdd-verifier, verifier, prompt, verify command, existing tests)\n2. **Created test plan** via TodoWrite\n3. **Wrote `tests/test-detection.test.ts`** — 52 tests covering isTestFile, isExcludedFile, isBarrelFile, isTypesOnlyFile, filterSourceFiles, findTestFiles, DEFAULT_TEST_DETECTION_CONFIG (ALL PASSING)\n4. **Wrote `tests/test-runner.test.ts`** — 22 tests covering parseTestCounts (Bun/Jest/unparseable), extractTestErrorSummary, runTests integration (ALL PASSING)\n5. **Wrote `tests/tdd-verifier.test.ts`** — 18 tests covering runTddVerification (skipping, execution, strict mode, summary), extractTddErrorSummary, renderTddVerificationReport (ALL PASSING)\n6. **Wrote `tests/prompt.test.ts`** — Tests for generatePrompt (basic structure, TDD section injection, subtasks, browser section), generateConflictResolutionPrompt (NOT YET RUN)\n\n### Still In Progress:\n- **Run `tests/prompt.test.ts`** — written but not yet executed/verified\n\n### Remaining TODO:\n- Run prompt tests and fix any failures (red → green)\n- **Commit test files** (first logical commit — all test files)\n- **Enhance test-detection.ts** — better detection of non-testable files (config, docs, .md, .json, .yml)\n- **Enhance prompt.ts** — strengthen TDD red-green cycle enforcement instructions\n- **Enhance verifier.ts/tdd-verifier.ts** — integration completeness\n- **Run `bun run build`** to verify final state\n- Make commits for implementation changes\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Read (existing code):\n- `package.json` — project config, scripts (build: `bun build`, test: `bun test`)\n- `src/config.ts` — WomboConfig type, TddConfig, DEFAULT_CONFIG, loadConfig, validateConfig\n- `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — git diff parsing, test file detection, exclusion logic, coverage reporting\n- `src/lib/test-runner.ts` — test command execution, output parsing (Bun/Jest formats)\n- `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — TDD verification orchestration, result types, summary building\n- `src/lib/verifier.ts` — full verification pipeline (build + browser + TDD), runFullVerification\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — agent prompt generation, TDD instructions, conflict resolution prompts\n- `src/commands/verify.ts` — verify CLI command with --skip-tests, --strict-tdd flags\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — handleBuildVerification function (lines 312-439)\n- `tests/features.test.ts` — existing test patterns/helpers\n- `tests/config.test.ts` — existing config tests\n- `tests/output.test.ts` — existing output tests\n- `tests/validate.test.ts` — existing validation tests\n\n### Created (new test files):\n- `tests/test-detection.test.ts` — 52 tests, ALL PASSING ✓\n- `tests/test-runner.test.ts` — 22 tests, ALL PASSING ✓\n- `tests/tdd-verifier.test.ts` — 18 tests, ALL PASSING ✓\n- `tests/prompt.test.ts` — written, NOT YET RUN\n\n### To be modified (implementation enhancements):\n- `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — enhance non-testable file exclusion\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — strengthen TDD enforcement instructions\n- `src/lib/tdd-verifier.ts` — potential integration improvements","time":{"start":