sts for them:\\n\\n- Documentation files (`.md`, `.mdx`, `.txt`)\\n- Configuration files (`.json`, `.yml`, `.yaml`, `.toml`, `.env`)\\n- Type declaration files (`.d.ts`)\\n- Re-export barrel files (`index.ts` with only `export ... from` statements)\\n- Types-only files (containing only `type`, `interface`, or `enum` declarations)\\n- Asset files (images, SVGs, CSS)\\n\\n### Verification\\n\\nAfter all changes are complete, the verification pipeline will automatically:\\n1. Run `bun test` and verify all tests pass\\n2. Check that every new/modified source file has a corresponding test file\\n3. Report coverage ratio of tested vs untested files\\n\\n**⚠️ Strict mode is active.** Verification will FAIL if any testable source file is missing a test.\\n\\n## Commit Guidelines\\n\\n- Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`, `docs(scope):`\\n- Scope should be: `test-feature` or a relevant module name\\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\\n- Do NOT squash all changes into one commit\\n- Do NOT push to remote -- the orchestrator handles that\\n- Do NOT modify `tasks` -- the orchestrator handles that\\n\\n## Execution\\n\\n1. Read the key files listed above to understand the codebase\\n2. Create a plan (use the TodoWrite tool)\\n3. Implement each subtask, committing as you go\\n4. Run `bun run build` to verify\\n5. If the build passes, you are done\\n6. If the build fails, fix the errors and re-run until it passes\"\n\n      at <anonymous> (/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/tdd-red-green-coercion/tests/prompt.test.ts:287:20)\n(fail) generatePrompt — TDD section > includes strict mode label when strictTdd is true [1.00ms]\n\n 154 pass\n 1 fail\n 277 expect() calls\nRan 155 tests across 4 files. [371.00ms]\n","title":"Run all TDD-related tests","metadata":{"output":"bun test v1.3.10 (30e609e0)\n\ntests/tdd-verifier.test.ts:\n\n  TDD: TDD disabled\n\n\n───────────────────────────────────────────────────